                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d903">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 E.W./11–2844</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Telephone Conversation, by the Assistant Chief
                        of the Division of British Commonwealth Affairs</hi> (<hi rend="italic"
                        >Achilles</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-06">December 6,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Ranken telephoned this afternoon, with reference to our conversation of
                    December 2, to say that the Embassy had now been advised that the British
                    Political Adviser at SHAEF had advised the Soviet Embassy in Paris of the
                    circumstances of the case and was awaiting an indication of the views of the
                    Soviet Government. I said that this would of course complicate the matter
                    considerably.</p>
            </div>
